# i18n & RTL

## Locales

Three locales: `/en`, `/fr`, `/ar`. Arabic is RTL.

## Translation Files

- `src/messages/en.json`, `src/messages/fr.json`, `src/messages/ar.json`
- Every new UI string must be added to ALL THREE files simultaneously
- Use `useTranslations('Namespace')` hook
- For arrays, use `t.raw('key')` and cast as `string[]`

## Language Quality Standards

When adding or updating translations, follow these rules strictly:

### English (en)
- Professional, concise, direct tone
- Stat labels must be descriptive (e.g. "Properties managed", not "Turnovers")
- CTAs should be action-oriented and clear

### French (fr)
- Proper French — never leave English words untranslated
- Use natural phrasing, not word-for-word translation from English
- CTAs should be short and punchy (e.g. "Estimation gratuite", not "Obtenir une estimation gratuite")
- "WhatsApp" stays as-is, but verbs must be French (e.g. "Discuter sur WhatsApp", not "Chat sur WhatsApp")

### Arabic (ar) — Darija (Moroccan Arabic)
- Use Darija consistently, NOT Modern Standard Arabic (MSA)
- Darija prepositions: "فـ" / "فال" (not "في"), "ديال" (not possessive construct), "بلا ما" (not "دون أن")
- Darija verbs: "كنتكلفو" / "كنديرو" / "كننسقو" / "هضر" (not MSA equivalents)
- Darija vocab: "مكتري" (not "مستأجر"), "الثمن" (not "السعر"), "كري" (not "إيجار")
- Keep technical terms that have no Darija equivalent (e.g. "check-in", "WhatsApp", "Airbnb")
- Numbers: use Arabic-Indic convention where natural ("+500" not "500+")

## Checklist for Every New Section

1. Write English copy first
2. Translate to proper French (no English leftovers)
3. Translate to Darija Arabic (no MSA)
4. Verify every key used in the component exists in all 3 files
5. Verify stat labels, CTA text, and aria labels are all translated

## RTL Rules

- `<html dir="rtl">` is set automatically for Arabic
- Never use `left`/`right` in CSS — use logical properties:
  - `ps-` / `pe-` (padding), `ms-` / `me-` (margin)
  - `inset-s-` / `inset-e-` (positioning)
  - `text-start` / `text-end`
  - `rounded-ss-` / `rounded-se-` / `rounded-es-` / `rounded-ee-`
- Arrow icons: `rtl:rotate-180`
- Drawer opens from left in RTL, right in LTR

## Routing

- Use `import { Link } from '@/i18n/routing'` (named import, not default)
- Locale segment is first path segment: `/{locale}/page`
